   <concept id="FAR_47_207_7" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">47.207-7</ph> Liability and insurance.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2742e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall specify-</p>
               <ol id="d2742e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                The contractor’s liability for injury to persons or damage to property other than the freight being transported;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e21">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contractor’s liability for loss of and/or damage to the freight being transported; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e26">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                The amount of insurance the contractor is required to maintain.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e31">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            When the contractor’s liability for loss of and/or damage to the freight being transported is not specified, the usual measure of liability as prescribed in section 11706 of the Interstate Commerce Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title49-section11706&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">49 U.S.C. 11706</xref>) applies.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e39">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.247-21.dita#FAR_52_247_21"
                        base="i1045769"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.247-21</xref>, Contractor Liability for Personal Injury and/or Property Damage.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e47">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.247-22.dita#FAR_52_247_22"
                        base="i1045781"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.247-22</xref>, Contractor Liability for Loss of and/or Damage to Freight other than Household Goods, in solicitations and contracts for the transportation of freight other than household goods.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e55">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.247-23.dita#FAR_52_247_23"
                        base="i1045790"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.247-23</xref>, Contractor Liability for Loss of and/or Damage to Household Goods, in solicitations and contracts for the transportation of household goods, including the rate per pound appropriate to the situation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e63">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
						            When freight is not shipped under rates subject to released or declared value, see <xref href="28.313.dita#FAR_28_313"
                        base="i1088051"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">28.313</xref>(a) and the clause at <xref href="52.228-9.dita#FAR_52_228_9"
                        base="i1051209"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.228-9</xref>, Cargo Insurance.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2769e74">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
						            When the contracting officer determines that vehicular liability and/or general public liability insurance required by law are not sufficient for a contract, see <xref href="28.313.dita#FAR_28_313"
                        base="i1088051"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">28.313</xref>(b) and the clause at <xref href="52.228-10.dita#FAR_52_228_10"
                        base="i1051223"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.228-10</xref>, Vehicular and General Public Liability Insurance.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
